> I hereby exercise my Right of Patronage under R1661 to pay out to Blob 1
> VT for voting on P3788.

I have serious doubts as to whether the Speaker can justify a belief
that Voting on a Proposal e authored can be considered an act "of
benefit to the Agora community". (It clearly doesn't constitute an
act that "exceed[s] the call of duty", or one of "extreme sacrifice
for the good of the game".) With Voting mechanisms being what they
are, it can be argued that not voting on a Proposal can indicate
opposition to that Proposal as well as indifference; and if part of
the community is opposed to a given Proposal, it is likely that
voting FOR is of benefit only to a particular subset of that
community.

This isn't to say I am opposed to using Patronage in this way,
because one of the things I like about the Patronage Rule is that it
leaves a lot to the Speaker's discretion, but I'd like to caution
the Speaker that 'wasting' Patronage on rewarding routine acts such
as Voting, and compounding the offence by making it look like a bribe
to vote on eir own Proposals, is likely to lose em my Vote in future
S-E Elections.


