Is that really so clear? I'll grant that it isn't an act of extreme
sacrifice for the good of the game, but I do believe that Blob's vote is
both beyond the call of duty and an act of benefit to the game. Since I
deplore the attitude that many Players seem to have of saving their
pennies for some non-existent rainy day to come, anyone who votes is, in
my view, setting a fine example. Furthermore, since P3788 failed, it
clearly remains the view of the Agoran community, at least for the
moment, that there is no duty to vote. Until such time as a Proposal
like 3788 is passed, voting will therefore remain an act which is beyond
the call of duty.

